            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am honored to be part of the Pathways family. It is a place where passion for learning thrives, where students are encouraged to reach their full potential, and where teachers are supported in their quest to make a positive impact.\nFrom the moment I joined the faculty, I have been continually impressed by the school's unwavering commitment to academic excellence, personal growth, and community spirit.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Pathways World School Gurgaon - Gangani"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "BISWADEV SENGUPTA"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-05-28",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Our son, Abhimanyu Sengupta completed his IBDP (grades 11 & 12) from PWS, graduated in 2023 and now is pursuing his undergraduate program in Economics at University of Bath in the UK.\nReturning back to India after 9 years abroad, we were worried about how he will adjust here. At PWS, all our fears and worries were laid to rest. It was an absolutely enriching experience for him, guided and mentored by all the superb teachers, aided by the world class facilities and an engaging academic environment.\nWe were extremely touched by the way Ms Manjula Shenoi (Principal, Senior School) and Ms Mona (DP coordinator) took such special interest in the progress and well being of every student. We were always so assured and at peace that our son was in their care.\nAnd all the teachers at PWS were so brilliant and helped Abhi navigate his gruelling IB DP course well.\nA sepcial acknowledgement for Mr. Praveen Mariadas who was Abhi's mentor and FT at PWS. His guidance helped Abhi adjust with the new settings very easily and kept him always motivated & focussed, getting the best out of him. Praveen Sir was always available for us parents for a chat to answer our queries (even at odd hours and on holidays as well) and give us regular updates about Abhi's progress.\n\nToday as Abhi is about to complete his 1st year at Bath, we feel very happy and blessed that we took the right decision of enrolling Abhi at PWS on our return to India, at a very critical juncture of his academic career.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
